<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="trick-n">trick <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /trɪk/    美 /trɪk/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>诡计；花招；恶作剧：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her tears were just a trick to deceive others.
她的眼泪只是骗人的诡计。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If the neighbours do not give any sweets, the children might <strong>play a trick on</strong> them.
如果邻居们不给糖果，孩子们就可以捉弄他们。</p><footer>人教③ – 1</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>戏法；把戏：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>perform magic tricks</strong>
表演魔术</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>技巧；诀窍：</strong></h4>
<p>a way of doing sth that works well; a good method：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Patience is <strong>the trick of</strong> doing this job well.
耐心是做好这份工作的诀窍。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— Could you tell me the <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (诀窍)of making such tasty cakes?
— Well, I just follow the directions in the cookbook.  （2014 福建改）<br />
A.feature<br />
B.plan<br />
C.cost<br />
D.trick  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. trick  </p></div>